  m_Name: Level_26_La Danta
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  levelNumber: 26
  levelName: La Danta
  location: "Pet\xE9n, Guatemala"
  levelDescription: "In the heart of El Mirador, La Danta towers as the giant of
    the Maya world.\n\nLa Danta, located in the El Mirador basin of northern Pet\xE9n,
    Guatemala, is one of the largest pyramids in the world by volume. Built during
    the Preclassic Period (c. 300 BC\u2013100 AD), it rises about 72 meters (236
    feet) above the jungle and covers a massive platform, making it a monumental
    achievement of Maya engineering.\r\n\r\nThe pyramid\u2019s name, La Danta (\u201CThe
    Tapir\u201D), reflects its immense size and strength. Archaeologists estimate
    that constructing La Danta required moving millions of stone blocks and organizing
    vast labor forces, showing the power and sophistication of El Mirador\u2019s
    rulers.\r\n\r\nLa Danta was part of a ceremonial complex that included plazas,
    causeways, and smaller temples, linking El Mirador to other Preclassic Maya centers.
    Its scale suggests the city was a major political and religious hub long before
    the Classic Period."
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: 34f4bcda39dadb140a2901ba3158f14f, type: 3}
